# Test the Supplier Communications Agent (production ready preview)

[!include [banner](../includes/banner.md)]
[!INCLUDE [preview-banner](~/../shared-content/shared/preview-includes/preview-banner.md)]
<!-- KFM: Preview until further notice -->

Learn how to test Emails from vendors with the Supplier Communications Agent in Microsoft Dynamics 365 Supply Chain Management.

The agent has two independent features:

- *Follow-up with vendors* (writing reminders)
- *Updates from vendors* (reading vendor emails).

For testing *Updates from vendors* (reading vendor emails), you can test the feature for a single email without having done the whole configuration, specially skipping the part where the shared mailbox or personal mailboxes are configured. 
This can be useful if you want to try the feature with a single email or just to show how the agent works. 

## Test the "Updates from vendors" (reading emails) feature without setup

Enable the feature in feature management *(Production Ready Preview) Supplier communications*
Go to *Procurement and sourcing > (Preview) Procurement Agent - Supplier Communications > (Preview) Emails from vendors*

You will see the workspace where the emails from vendors would come if you had configured it with a configuration. Here you can just try with a single email by clicking:
1. *Add vendor messages* on the top menu
2. Enter a *Title*: the email title of an existing email you would like to try the agent with, either a real or a test one you can make up
3. Enter the *Message*: enter the body of the email
4. Enter an *Attachment*: optionally, enter an attachment if desired, it can be an image or a PDF. 
5. Click *Save*
6. Wait for a few minutes and refres the page, it will show the email you just send to the agent
